
XKB is the basic → hardware/keyboard mapping package for → Linux/X. It's used to define → Linux/keyboard/layout[keyboard layouts].

The configuration files for XKB are apparently located under → Linux/fhs/usr/share/X11/xkb

The XKB equivalent of → Linux/shell/commands/xmodmap is `xkbcomp`.

{ Components

  A keyboard layout is defined by five components
    • Keycodes: the mapping of a keyboard's → hardware/keyboard#scancode[scanecode] to a symbolic name.
    • Types
    • Compat
    • Symbols
    • Geometry

}

{ Parameters

  XKB Parameters are:
    • XkbRules
    • XkbModel
    • XkbLayout
    • XkbVariant
    • XkbOptions

}

